- "recording" refers to audio files of bird songs or calls;
- "average duration" is calculated by summing the durations of all recordings for a species and dividing by the number of recordings.

- 'Soundscapes' refers to the spectrograms generated from audio files;
- 'Magicians' refers to the users who performed the processing;
- 'Enchanted' refers to the date when the processing occurred;
- 'Precious recordings' refers to audio files with a high-quality spectrogram.

